 Bart Hobijn, Peter Howitt, Hehui Jin, Charles I. Jones, Michael Kumhof, Mordecai Kurz, David Laibson, Lars Ljungqvist, N. Gregory Mankiw, Dale T. Mortensen, Maurizio Motolese, Stephen Nickell, Luca Nunziata, Wolfgang Ochel, Christopher A. Pissarides, Glenda Quintini, Ricardo Reis, Andrea Repetto, Thomas J. Sargent, Jeremy Tobacman, and Gianluca Violante. Commenting are Olivier J. Blanchard, Jean-Paul Fitoussi, Mark Gertler, Robert E. Hall, Robert E. Lucas, Jr., David H. Papell, Robert A. Pollak, Robert M. Solow, Nancy L. Stokey, and Lars E. O. Svensson. Also included are reflections by Phelps, a preface by Paul A. Samuelson, and the editors' introduction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aEconomistszUnited StatesvCongresses. 0aMacroeconomicsvCongresses. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / General.2bisacsh  aArgentina.  aBaxter-Stockman puzzle.  aBrowning, M.  aCanada, investment in.  aCarlstrom, C.  aDixit-Stiglitz model.  aDrazen, A.  aFinland, unions in.  aFriedman, Milton.  aInternet usage.  aOlson, Mancur.  aaccelerationist Phillips curve.  aadvertising expenditures.  aanonymity.  aassessment variables.  aaverage opinion.  abalanced growth path (BGP).  abankruptcy.  abehavioral economics.  abelief structure.  achannel capacities.  acommon knowledge.  aconstant-gain algorithm.  adebt puzzle.  adisability benefits.  adisequilibrium.  aefficiency wages.  aelectricity.  aentrepreneurial thesis.  aequity premium puzzle.  aexcess returns puzzle.  aexponential discount functions.  afinancial accelerator.  ageographic mobility.  ahabit formation.  ahigher-order beliefs.  ahyperbolic time preferences.  ahyperinflation.  aimperfect knowledge.  aincentive wages.  ainfinite-regress problem.  ainflation inertia.  ainflation models.  a